Here's a code example in JavaScript using Discord.js v14 to create a Discord bot with a ban command and slash commands:

// Import the Discord.js v14 module
const Discord = require('discord.js');

// Set up a new client object
const client = new Discord.Client();

// Register the bot's commands
client.commands = new Discord.Collection();

// Create a command for the ban command
client.commands.set('ban', {
  description: 'Ban a user from the server.',
  execute: async (message, args) => {
    // Check if the user has permission to use the command
    if (!message.member.hasPermission('BAN_MEMBERS')) {
      message.reply('You do not have permission to use this command.');
      return;
    }

    // Get the user to ban from the message object
    const target = message.mentions.users.first();
    if (!target) {
      message.reply('Please specify the user to ban by mentioning them in this message.');
      return;
    }

    // Ban the target user from the server with a reason 
    await message.guild.members.ban(target, { reason: 'Banned by command.' });

    // Send a reply to the user with the success message 
    message.reply(`User ${target} has been banned from the server.`);    
  }  
}); 
```  Here's an example of how to use it: 1) Create a new Discord bot and connect it to your Discord server using Discord.js v14; 2) Run the code above in a new file and save it as "ban-command-example"; 3) Copy and paste the code into your bot's source code directory; 4) Save the file and restart your bot; 5) Test your bot by invoking its ban command using slash commands (e.g., /ban @username).

